Rating: 4
This is my favorite cake, I have been making it for years. It is easy to do and always gets stellar reviews. It can be served plain or dressed... in the summer, I plate it with raspberry sauce, or a sauce of fresh figs, both delightful complements. Today, I am pairing it with home-made ginger ice cream.

Rating: 4
I made this for my mom's birthday and everyone loved it! Very easy to make, does not require expensive ingredients. It was even better the next day, very moist. This recipe is a keeper.

Rating: 4
I made this for my grandparents, and my grandmother, almost a trained chef, loved it. She ate every crumb off her plate. I used 7 oz semi-sweet and 1 oz unsweetened with an extra tablespoon of sugar in the butter; worked fine. It almost has a brownie texture but so much more sophisticated. Very rich and tender. Make a doily pattern with the powdered sugar on top and you are set.

