Rating: 3
I have visited Capri many times and I always look forward to eating the wonderful chocolate and lemon tortes served at most restaurants and cafes on the island. I have made this recipe 3 times and it has always turned out great. My friends and family will attest to that! The recipe is time consuming though, so don't plan to make it if you're in a hurry. In my experience, the cake is better served the second day. I think that waiting atleast 12-24 hours allows the flavors to really develop.